Automatically Collected Information 

    Mobile advertising SDK within our application may use GPS technology (or other similar technology) to determine your current location in order to display a location map with relevant advertisements. You can refuse the access to this information in your device settings.

    We use Android Advertising ID to collect information about the users actions that took place because of the advertising. Advertising IDs are user-specific, resettable IDs provided by Google Play services for advertising. These IDs give rights to the developers, to monetize digital activities through apps. 
    An Android Advertising ID is somewhat analogous to a third-party advertising cookie, in that it enables an advertiser to understand that a user of a particular phone has taken an ad action like a click on a banner or an app install.
    You can reset your advertising ID or opt out of interest-based ads at any time, right from the Google Settings app.

We use the information collected through the application:

a) to communicate with you;
b) to improve the application according to your requests;
c) to perform marketing analysis, to help us understand how the application is being used, such as the frequency and duration of usage;
d) to assist you with our product;
e) to enforce our Terms of Service and other usage polices.

We may also store some information locally on your device. For example, we may store information as local cache so that you can open the app and view content faster. Cache saving properties can be changed in application settings. 


